Instructions for running the script

This works on a clean Ubuntu 24.04 server, 
Open the terminal, best using SSH.

Create a new script file (you can choose any name, example: install-crm.sh):

sudo nano install-crm.sh

Copy the entire script code (the full block I gave you) and paste it inside the editor.
Save and exit nano:
Press Ctrl + O → Enter → Ctrl + X
Make the file executable:

sudo chmod +x install-crm.sh

Run the script:

sudo ./install-crm.sh

What happens next:
The script asks a few questions.
Most of the time you can just press Enter to accept the default values.
It will ask for:
Install path → press Enter (uses /var/www/html/crm)
Server IP/domain → press Enter (uses your server's IP)
Admin username → press Enter (uses "admin") or type your preferred name
Admin password → press Enter (auto-generates a strong one)
MariaDB/MySQL root password → press Enter (auto-generates)
Database user → press Enter (uses "suitecrm") or type your own
Database user password → press Enter (auto-generates)

At the end it asks: Proceed? [Y/n] → press Enter (or Y)

After the script finishes:
Open your browser and go to:
http://your-server-ip (the IP shown earlier)
Log in with the admin username and admin password shown at the end of the script output.
Important: Write down or copy the passwords shown in the final summary (admin + database + root).
